                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "non- bijective version of Wigner's theorem states that every (not necessarily bijective) transformation of the pure state space preserving the transition probability, i.e. the angles between rays, is induced by a linear or conjugate- linear isometry. On the other hand, Uhlhorn's version of Wigner's theorem [23] says that every bijective transformation preserving the orthogonality of rays in both directions is induced by a unitary or anti- unitary operator if "
                                },
                                {
